@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "PentA" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed. The only requirement is that you need to have an 8 (or more)
colour Workbench.

                             How to play?

  To play, move all 12 shapes so that they all fit in the rectangular
pattern displayed in the center of the game area. You can place the
shapes everywhere you want on the game board, except when a shape
will overlap part of another or the game border. 

  -To @{b}rotate@{ub} a shape, just click and release the mouse button on a
   part of a shape, if a rotation is possible (meaning that there are
   no obstructions like another neighbouring shape in the way or the
   game border is far enough), the shape will rotate clockwise by 90
   degrees around the tile you clicked on.

  -To @{b}move@{ub} a shape, just click on any part of a shape you want to move
   and release the mousebutton on an empty space where you want to
   place that shape, if the move is possible (no interfering shapes
   or border) the shape will go there.

  -To @{b}invert@{ub} a shape, click on any part of the shape and release the
   mousebutton on another part of the same shape, this will 'swap'
   both tiles of that shape and in the same way 'mirror' the rest of
   that shape.

  Try to complete the game in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS:

  There are 4 different board sizes to choose from: a 3 x 20 board,
a 4 x 15 board, a 5 x 12 board and a 6 x 10 board. Just click on the
'3 x 20 Penta' gadget (or whatever size happens to be displayed at
the time) and the game will cycle between the board sizes and change
the board size area accordingly.

  You can restart a game anytime by clicking on the 'New Game' gadget
(or in the '@{b}Game@{ub}' pull-down menu, select '@{b}New Game@{ub}', you can also use
the @{b}Right-Amiga@{ub} and '@{b}N@{ub}' keys).

@endnode

